subSubSection.paragraph:
Anal appendages
(
Figs 10–12
). Cerci creamy white, approximately 1.5x length of S10, with ventrolateral black tooth about one-fifth from base, short and turned outward; in dorsal view (
Fig. 10
) constricted in the middle, apical half slender. Epiproct black, wider than long, approximately 0.7x length of S10 and 0.4x of cerci, lateral lobes diverging with blunt tips; the median cleft U-shaped and shallow in ventral view, covered with minute setae, widening toward apex (
Figs 11–12
).
